claim.claim-text:
3. A method for applying active compression-decompression to an infant comprising:
obtaining a device comprising a first sleeve configured for placement over a medical assistance provider's first thumb and a second sleeve for placement over a medical assistance provider's second thumb, said first and second sleeves each being associated with at least one pad comprising an adhering material, wherein said first and second sleeves are coupled with a common pad or a different pad;
inserting said first and second thumbs into first and second sleeves, respectively;
adhering said device to an infant's chest in need of compression-decompression; and
using said device to apply active compression-decompression.
